---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
        The Filecoin Data Portal is a fully open and local friendly data
        platform that unifies Filecoin data from diverse sources (on-chain and
        off-chain). It is an instance of <a
            href="https://github.com/datonic/datadex">Datadex</a
        >.
    </p>

    <h3>How much do these datasets cost?</h3>
    <p>
        All of these datasets are free to use. They are available to the anyone
        at no cost without any warranties or guarantees of any kind, either
        expressed or implied. By using these datasets, you agree that you do so
        at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h3>Are there any restrictions on how these datasets can be used?</h3>
    <p>
        All of these datasets can be used without restriction. They are released
        under a <a href="https://creativecommons.org/public-domain/cc0/"
            >CC0 license into the public domain</a
        >.
    </p>

    <h3>Who is using these datasets?</h3>
    <p>
        Datasets produced by the Filecoin Data Portal are used by a wide range
        of organizations and individuals. Some of the use cases include:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a href="https://pulse.filecoindataportal.xyz/">Filecoin Pulse</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://numbers.filecoindataportal.xyz/"
                >Filecoin In Numbers</a
            >.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://dune.com/kalen/filecoin-daily-metrics"
                >Dune Dashboard</a
            >.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://www.reppo.ai/models"
                >Reppo Storage Provider's Reputation models</a
            >.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://fidl.tech">FIDL</a>'s <a
                href="https://compliance.allocator.tech/report/f03014641/1723421684/report.md"
                >Allocators Compilance reports</a
            >.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How does the data get updated?</h3>
    <p>
        The data is updated on a daily basis via GitHub Actions. You can see
        <a href="https://github.com/davidgasquez/filecoin-data-portal/actions"
            >every run and their logs on the repository</a
        >.
    </p>

    <h3>How can I get the data?</h3>
    <p>
        The data is available in multitude of formats. Go to the <a
            href="/data.html">datasets page</a
        > and select the one that suits your needs! If that's not enough, <a
            href="https://github.com/davidgasquez/filecoin-data-portal/issues/new"
            >open an issue</a
        > and we'll help you out!
    </p>

    <h3>Who is behind this project?</h3>
    <p>
        This project is maintained by <a href="https://davidgasquez.com/"
            >David Gasquez</a
        > thanks to <a href="https://protocol.ai/blog/pl-past-present-future/"
            >Protocol Labs blue funds</a
        > and <a href="https://www.fil-retropgf.io/"
            >Filecoin Retroactive Public Goods Funding</a
        > programs.
    </p>
</Layout>
